{"id":"9450","name":"Subscription renew reminder","tagline":"Reminds you when subscriptions renews","icon":"ios14 c4274264319 g61440","latest":"28237","description":"\n\t\t\t\t\t<p>Before using this shortcut, you have to create a list named “Subscriptions” in the reminders app.</p>\n<p>This shortcut creates reminders that will remind you when your free trial is ending, and the subscription is about to renew.</p>\n<p>If you for example start an Apple Music free trial that lasts for 3 months, you can run the shortcut and enter for example “Apple Music” for the name. In the duration option, you can select “months”, and choose either to be reminded the same day it renews, or two days before. (I recommend two days before). </p>\n<p>You have to select exactly one of the options marked with red, and exactly one of the options marked with green.</p>\n<p>After pressing “Done”, you will be asked how many months until receiving the reminding. In this case, you should enter “3”.</p>\n<p>When the shortcut is done, you should have a reminder with the name “Apple Music” in the reminders app, that will remind you exactly three months later.</p>\n<p>It is also possible to set the end date manually, instead of just adding days/weeks/months/years to the current date, by selecting “End date”</p>\n\t\t\t\t","releasenotes":"<p><strong>1.0 - June 16, 2021, 6:22 p.m.</strong></p>"}